This article doesn&#8217;t seem negative to me at all : it&#8217;s saying that prospects for money-launderers to use BitCoins are better than one might think.<br />
What it doesn&#8217;t say is that each time one of these &#8220;user friendly&#8221; interfaces crops up, it introduces a new way for hackers to infiltrate the system and fleece the unwary.<br />
Leave the crypto-geek currency to the cryto-geeks, I say.</p>
